<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12029q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12029q">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12029q"> 29(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Tiberius fells their forests</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Leur puissance a constamment subsist&eacute; jusqu&apos;&agrave; la conqu&ecirc;te des Gaules par les Romains, &amp; ils continu&egrave;rent encore l&apos;exercice de leur religion pendant pr&egrave;s de soixante ans, jusqu&apos;au tems o&ugrave; Tib&egrave;re, craignant qu&apos;elle ne f&ucirc;t une occasion de r&eacute;volte, fit massacrer les pr&ecirc;tres Druides, & raser les bois dans lesquels ils rendoient leur culte. <br><font color="green">[Their power has constantly subsisted until the conquest of Gaul by the Romans, &amp; they still continued to practice their religion for about sixty years, until <mark>Tiberius</mark>, fearing it could be an occasion for revolt, gave the order to slaughter the Druid priests, &amp; to <mark>fell the forests</mark> in which they practiced their cult.]</font> <small> M. Sabbathier, <a name="MSAD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MSAD"><cite title="source">Dictionnaire pour l'intelligence des auteurs classiques, Grecs et Latins</cite></a> (1773) 495-496</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12013e" href="c12all.htm#c12013e">VI.C.12:013(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
